commentary: Chigumbura to Mahmudullah, no run sooo close to short midwicket! The even evokes a reaction out of the normally stoic Zimbabwe coach, Mangongo! It was a slower ball on middle and the batsman opted to flick it away. He was way too early into the stroke and the ball lobs up and hung in the air for ages. Yet it wasn't quite long enough for Chatara at short midwicket to run to his left and try and do something about that

commentary: Jubair Hossain to Maruma, OUT bowled him! It's the wrong 'un, and it's surprised Maruma, who went back and across, maybe to punch the ball through the covers. Lovely way to get your first ODI wicket
